The source water for the AWTP will be recycled water produced by Tapia, which isfairly constant. The influent flow to Tapia varies due to the daily diurnal flow pattern.Additionally, during wet weather events, flows can significantly increase due to infiltration andinflow during and after rain. In the past, these influences have more than doubled the daily flowsat the treatment plant during winter storm events; however, these increased flows drop backdown to normal within a few dry days. The AWTP is intended to operate during the winterwhen recycled water demand is minimal and the likelihood of winter storms could occur.Consequently, this study will look at equalizing the influent flow to Tapia. The Consultant shall: Review recorded wet weather flow to the Tapia and identify 50-year and 100-yearstorm events Review available water quality of influent flow to Tapia during 50-year and 100-yearstorm events Estimate peak storm water quantity to Tapia Determine the recommended volume for a tank needed to equalize wet weather flowto Tapia Estimate blended water quality (following equalization) for treatment at the AWTP Evaluate location for the Equalization Basin including but not limited to; existingunused tank(s) at Tapia, land currently used for storage adjacent to Tapia andowned by the JPA, and Recycled Water Reservoir # 1, which is currently not in usebut owned by the JPA Identify preliminary options and costs associated with facilities needed to properlyequalize the influent flow Conduct a present worth analysis of equalization options including estimated capitalcost, Operation and Maintenance costs, replacement costs and residual asset value. Recommend the best option for influent flow equalization.Task 1B - Environmental Constraints AnalysisAn environmental constraints analysis will be conducted to assist the JPA in identifying keyenvironmental issues that should be given due consideration during the design phase of theequalization basin. The analysis is intended to assist the JPA in evaluating equalization basinalternatives. The constraints analysis will cover all the resource areas of the State CaliforniaEnvironmental Quality Act (CEQA) Guidelines Initial Study Checklist, which includes:Aesthetics, Agricultural and Forestry Resources, Air Quality, Biological Resources, CulturalResources, Geology and Soils, Greenhouse Gas Emissions, Hazards and Hazardous Materials,Hydrology and Water Quality, Land Use and Planning, Mineral Resources, Noise, Populationand Housing, Public Services, Recreation, Transportation/Traffic, and Utilities and ServiceSystems. Prepare a draft Initial Study Checklist to serve as the basis for CEQA compliance4. Rank various equalization basin alternatives in terms of potential environmental impacts: low-probability of significant impacts, moderate (potential for significant impacts but which could be mitigated), high (significant and immitigable impacts).5.
